      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ADA BLAZE (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.25 beating Rio Lulu. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Hard to go past. ZIPPING BELUGA (4) is yet to miss the placings in an excellent record this trip which boasts two wins and two placings. Recorded a nose win (17.50) in a Grade 6 last time at this track. Looks one of the chances. JUST A PIRATE (2) had been in super honest form hitting the frame three times on end before finishing fifth (22.79) at Murray Bridge last time. Has ability and is one of the better chances. WOW HIS NORM (8) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
